<subSubSection id="13F039E49CD175D60C2A2CC505D8CF99" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="notes">
<paragraph id="DCB356A08CC0A413CA5F78EEAF23F192" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BF5347004767A3F606CB262A1C048BA4" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
In the protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="5FAF769BED37902540267F5C0D27384A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Cryptantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cryptantha argentea" order="Boraginales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="argentea">
<emphasis id="4D48AFBF05D925E6DF17437EE3B4BBCF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Cryptantha argentea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="38C5C316F1993FB5FEE4575BC980A1FF" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
cited a collection he made near Aguada Grande, Chile, and explicitly stated that the type was lodged at GH. Two duplicates of the gathering 
<emphasis id="09D7263C3F23F1A546C4AF43E3023981" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Johnston 5814</emphasis>
are found there in agreement with the protologue as referred to by 
<bibRefCitation id="EDCE1C769B55A91F345DCC55DBC069DE" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">Johnston (1927)</bibRefCitation>
. Thus, 
<bibRefCitation id="BB8FDFDAE54CD60079C022B13634906D" author="Johnston, IM" journalOrPublisher="Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B16" refString="Johnston, IM, 1927. Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae. Contributions from the Gray Herbarium of Harvard University 78: 1 - 118" title="Studies in the Boraginaceae VI. A revision of the South American Boraginoideae." volume="78" year="1927">
<normalizedToken id="B1B5CA0F7E9F60C9DC7CE45D9E36DD5A" originalValue="Johnston’s">Johnston's</normalizedToken>
(1927)
</bibRefCitation>
statement is insufficiently precise since it cannot be ascertained to which of the two specimens at GH he was referring. In this context, the sheet GH00011520 is selected as lectotype of the name.
</paragraph>
